parameters: \pop[2]As many people say though, the unknown is alluring. That's part of why I'm sitting here right now.
\pop[2]It was a long walk to the nightclub, but we didn't feel like driving or using public transit.
That's the best you could come up with?
\pop[3]Speaking of which, I still need to yell at Dante.
\pop[3]I heard that noise when you connected to our speakers, dude.
Was I not clear enough the other day? \c[14]Don't\c[0] mess with my mods.
It's just been a while since anyone connected like that.
I made those changes months ago.
\pop[3]Is that supposed to get you off the hook...?
\pop[2]Dante scoffs, and looks the other way.
\pop[4]You know, I might not drink as much as I thought tonight.
\pop[4]Yeah, because you won't get off my back.
\pop[4]Is it too much to ask for just one night of fun?
You're the one who wanted that, yet you're tearing into me.
\pop[2]An awkward silence fills the air as they stare at one another.
\pop[2]But just like usual, they erupt into laughter only a few moments later
\pop[3]Fine, fine. I'll try to ease up on you a little bit.
If we want to be friends forever, I might just have to.
\pop[2]All of a sudden, I start to think about the conversation we had earlier.
\pop[2]In their visions, they were no longer in touch. No longer a friend group.
\pop[4]You really think we can pull that off...?
\pop[2]Isaac stops in his tracks, and turns to face all of us.
\pop[4]Shame. Always wanted to do one of those.
\pop[3]I'd rather not have your \c[10]blood on my hands\c[0], Taylor.
\pop[4]But I thought we were finally bonding!
\pop[3]Come on; can you \c[14]please\c[0] take this seriously for a second?
I just want to make sure that we don't all drift apart.
\pop[4]And how do you suggest we do that?
\pop[3]Let's promise to keep using it, no matter where we are.
Even if it's just one or two messages a week. No pressure, right?
\pop[3]Then we really can be friends forever.
\pop[3]Right now, you're all important to me. I think about you all the time.
But in my vision, like I said, I'm not even aware of your existence.
\pop[4]Tragic. Everybody should know who I am.
But on a more serious note, I guess I can manage that.
\pop[4]Yeah. I don't plan on leaving the group, so I'm down.
\pop[2]He puts out his hand, palm facing down.
\pop[2]One by one, we stack our hands ontop of his.
\pop[2]I wait until the end, since I'm the newest one here.
\pop[2]We all say that in unison, and look at each other with big smiles.
\pop[2]A moment later, we pull back our hands, and continue on our way.
\pop[2]I had no problem with the agreement, since it seemed pretty low maintenance.
\pop[2]It's a little odd, but this "pact" suddenly made my life feel more grounded.
\pop[2]If we really followed through, I'd always have friends to support me.
\pop[2]That made this scary new city seem all the more inviting.
\pop[2]By the time the night was over, this place would be home.
\pop[2]I decide to bring up something that my counselor told me at our session.
\pop[2]There's a theory that \c[17]Komorebi\c[0] isn't set in stone. It's just a "possibility".
\pop[2]A pact like this could very well defy what they believed to be fate.
\pop[4]If that's true, then I'm screwed no matter what.
If you're my best friends, then this is clearly the darkest timeline.
\pop[2]I notice that Dante looks a little worried.
\pop[4]You know your counselor isn't supposed to do that, right?
He's supposed to stick to facts, and \c[23]Argus\c[0]-approved exercises.
I may be wrong, but I'm pretty sure that's "off curriculum", so to speak.
\pop[4]Yeah; and that could only come from someone who's never had a vision.
\pop[4]People like us, who live with \c[17]Komorebi\c[0], kind of find that laughable.
It's something you can't understand. Not unless you've lived it.
\pop[2]I ask him for some clarification, as I'm a little confused.
\pop[4]Well I didn't have a speech prepared, or anything.
But it'd be like hosting a lecture on something you know nothing about.
And not only that; but your students are already experts on the subject.
\pop[3]Think about it this way. It's inescapable, even if you escape it.
We could defy our vision, sure, but we still have to experience it.
Every day, we face the future as if it were the present.
\pop[3]It's indistinguishable from reality, and it's awful.
So even if we are friends forever? I'll still lose you all the time.
Who cares if it's another world, or universe? The feelings are all real.
\pop[2]I guess I never thought of it that way before.
\pop[2]Even if we learn the origin of these visions, they'll still happen every day.
\pop[2]They'd exist alongside the truth, and probably even overpower it.
\pop[4]Though I have to say, we should probably change the subject.
This whole thing seems like a recipe for depression. Let's not sabotage our night out, huh?
\pop[4]True. And honestly, thanks for your input, Delta.
I know that you were only trying to help out.
\pop[2]I nod, and tell him it's fine.
\pop[2]It's true, though. It wasn't my place to speak about \c[17]Komorebi\c[0].
\pop[2]Building off of that lecture metaphor, I should be sitting and listening.
\pop[3]Whoa. Didn't expect such a big lineup.
\pop[2]We round the next corner, and I see the nightclub for the first time.
\pop[2]For some reason, it looks exactly how I expected it would.
\pop[2]But Isaac was right. The lineup was massive.
\pop[4]I thought you said they cancelled the event.
\pop[3]They did. I guess this is just the kind of traffic they get.
It's the most popular club in town, after all.
Any chance your friend can help with the line?
Let me go talk to the person at the door.
\pop[2]Isaac motions for us to wait, as he approaches the club.
\pop[2]We stand around, and exchange glances with one another.
\pop[2]Dante still looks worried, and inches closer toward me.
\pop[4]You know, I was serious about what I said.
\pop[4]Your counselor isn't supposed to talk about that kinda stuff.
If you reported him, you might be able to get cleared as a patient.
\pop[2]And I doubt that reporting him would get me cleared.
\pop[2]They'd probably just transfer me over to somebody else.
\pop[2]I'm already making progress with him, so I can't do that.
\pop[2]Starting all over with another counselor would be super tedious.
\pop[2]Dante nods as I speak my thoughts. He seems to understand.
\pop[4]Well, sometimes these things benefit other people.
\pop[4]You might be fine, but he's still breaking the rules. That could be harmful.
It's not a good thing to fill people's heads with nonsense. Especially in therapy.
\pop[2]He has a point. But before we can talk any further, Isaac returns.
\pop[3]Good news. We get to skip the line.
\pop[4]Woo! And all of a sudden, your friend is back in my good books.
\pop[2]The mood of the group instantly skyrockets.
\pop[2]Waiting in a long line would've honestly killed the flow of our evening.
\pop[2]Thankfully, Isaac's friend planned around that fact.
\pop[4]Well then, what kind of drink should we order first...?
\pop[2]That question lingers as we make our way inside the nightclub.
\pop[2]A few people complain that we're able to skip the line. It's kind of flattering.
\pop[2]I have no right to feel this way, but it makes me feel important, and special.
